Certain Subsidiaries to Join in Subsidiary Guaranty
 
opinion of counsel as the Global Agent shall reasonably request, in each case, in form and substance satisfactory to the Global Agent; , , that, notwithstanding the foregoing or anything else in this Agreement to the contrary, (i) neither the Receivables Subsidiary nor AGSC shall be required to become a Subsidiary Guarantor hereunder so long as the Permitted Receivables Facility shall not have been terminated, and (ii) a Subsidiary shall not be required to become a party to the Subsidiary Guaranty or a Foreign Subsidiary Guaranty, as applicable, so long as (A) the total assets of such Subsidiary shall be less than $5,000,000, and (B) the aggregate of the total assets of all such Subsidiaries with total asset values of less than $5,000,000 that are not parties to the Subsidiary Guaranty or a Foreign Subsidiary Guaranty, as applicable, shall not exceed $50,000,000.
