Yield Rate
"" shall be equal to (i) the sum of the Aggregate Investment and the LC Amount multiplied by (ii) a percentage equal to (A) the Yield Reserve Percentage divided by (B) 100% minus the Yield Reserve Percentage.
Yield Reserve
"" means, on any date, an amount equal to (i) the sum of the Base Rate as of the end of the most recent period plus 1.5%, multiplied by (ii) the product of 1.5 times the Days Sales Outstanding, divided by (iii) 360.
